    "created_at": "2017-03-06T18:17:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-06T18:17:49Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There's a difference between a dynamic failure of an RPC and a misuse of the API. An error caused by passing an incorrectly typed parameter should be corrected by the programmer, by changing the code, so it shouldn't matter where the error comes out. The difference is that if we throw the error instead of passing it to the callback, it's harder to accidentally ignore it."
